1 B. After the effective date of this act, institutions of higher
2 education within The Oklahoma State System of Higher Education shall
3 initiate a review of diversity, equity, and inclusion positions,
4 departments, activities, procedures, and programs and, if deemed
5 necessary, restructure or eliminate functions that are not necessary
6 for compliance, accreditation, or student or employee support
7 services intended to broadly support success.
8 C. Nothing in this section shall be construed to limit or
9 prohibit institutions of higher education within The Oklahoma State
10 System of Higher Education, including any agency of the executive
11 branch supporting those institutions’ work, from applying for a
12 grant or complying with the accreditation requirements of an
13 accrediting or licensing agency including, but not limited to,
14 submitting to the grantor or accreditation agency a statement that:
15 1. Highlights the institution’s or agency’s work in supporting:
16 a. first-generation college students,
17 b. students from low-income families,
18 c. students with unique abilities, or
19 d. underserved student populations; or
20 2. Certifies compliance with applicable anti-discrimination
21 laws, rules, and regulations.
22 D. The provisions of this section shall not be construed to
23 apply to institutions of higher education within The Oklahoma State
24 System of Higher Education with respect to:
SB796 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 1. A policy, practice, procedure, program, class, or activity
2 required for compliance with state or federal laws, rules, or
3 regulations for obtaining or retaining institutional, academic, or
4 discipline-specific accreditation or licensure;
5 2. The academic freedom of any individual faculty member to
6 direct the instruction within his or her own course;
7 3. Scholarly research or creative work by an institution of
8 higher education’s students, faculty, or other research personnel or
9 the dissemination of such research or work;
10 4. An activity of a student organization registered with or
11 recognized by an institution of higher education;
12 5. Guest speakers or performances on short-term engagements;
13 6. Academic support, tutoring, and career services and student
14 success centers, so long as the programming is designed and
15 implemented without regard to race, sex, color, national origin, or
16 ethnicity;
17 7. Data collection; or
18 8. Access programs for military, veterans, Pell Grant
19 recipients, first-generation college students, students from low-
20 income families, students with unique abilities, or underserved
21 student populations.
22 E. By July 1, 2026, and each July 1 thereafter, institutions of
23 higher education within The Oklahoma State System of Higher
24 Education shall electronically submit to the Governor, the President
