1 Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker of the House of
2 Representatives a certificate of compliance with the provisions of
3 this section.
4 F. Nothing in this section shall be construed to prohibit the
5 promotion of civil discourse, debate, or speech that is protected by
6 the First Amendment to the United States Constitution.
7 G. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education may
8 promulgate rules to implement the provisions of this section.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
10 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
11 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
12 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
13 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
